#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:25
msgid "This section covers the three main ways to display movie data and some related options in Lumière."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:27
msgid "Lumiere Movies is a plugin under intense development; this help section might be innacurate with regard to the latest functions. Main functions of the plugin are explained below, aiming to be as much user-friendly as possible."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:45
msgid "The first way to use Lumiere Movies is to add links to movie titles that opens popups with information about that very same movies. It is a usefull for posts that mention movies title; just add a link to your movie title, and let visitors knowing more about the details of the movie you mention."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:47
msgid "Popup is a window that opened on click, which allows to consult director's and movie's information; if browsing a movie, one can read more about the movie but also the people who took part in the movie, such as actors, directors, etc."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:49
msgid "How to make a popup link"
msgstr ""

#. translators: %1$s and %2$s are HTML tags
#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:53
#, php-format
msgid "To create a link to a popup window, you only need to put the %1$smovie's title%2$s inside dedicated tags. Depending on the visual interface you use (modern WordPress, wysiwig old WordPress, or pure text interface), you may add these tags in different ways."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:57
msgid "If you use a recent WordPress and have not activated a plugin to continue using the old editor interface, you can add a Lumière link to a popup by selecting the title of your movie, then adding the link with the dedicated contextual menu option:"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:65
msgid "If you use an old WordPress version or a recent WordPress with the plugin 'classic editor' installed, you can access in the dedicated menu to 'add a popup link:"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:73
msgid "No explanation is need for those who prefer to write directly in HTML editor; it goes without saying they know how to add an HTML tag. But even in that interface a button is available for adding the code. For references, here is the HTML tag to wrap your movie's title with:"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:82
msgid "Whatever the tool you prefer, when you add such a link a small icon confirming that the link is Lumière compliant is added to your movie's title."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:95
msgid "Including movie information within your article is quite useful; it can ingeniously illustrate your post, displays crucial data (directors, actors) and at the same time add links to further popups that include even more detailed information."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:100
msgid "Lumière provides you with tools to add 'HTML tags' (span) to wrapp your movie's title when writting your article. These 'HTML tags' will be then converted into movie's details. In the same way as for for popups, three tools are provided depending upon your the WordPress interface you used to publish your posts. If you use the modern WordPress interface, a Lumière block is provided; just enter the movie's title or IMDb id, and you are done!"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:102
msgid "Lumiere Movies Inside a post using gutenberg block"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:104
msgid "You can add as many blocks as you whish; there is no limitation in the number of movies you can display per article."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:110
msgid "How to display data inside my post - advanced users"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:120
msgid "The first filter to use is 'lum_find_movie_id' (as you probably do not know the movie's IMDb ID). It will return an array with the movie's imdb id, that you can use in a second filter 'lum_display_movies_box':"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:140
msgid "I want to get rid of thoses links opening popups"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:141
msgid "It could happen you do not want popups at all. Since by default Lumière Movies adds links whenever relevant to movie's details inside your article, you may change that behaviour. In order to do so, look for 'Main options / Advanced / Remove popup links' and uncheck the box. No links will be displayed, both for the widget and within your articles."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:154
msgid "Widgets are widely used in WordPress. It allows to select which information display in a given area, usually in the sidebar. Lumière allows to display any movie into your sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:158
msgid "How to use the widget"
msgstr ""

#. translators: %1$s to %6$s are HTML tags
#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:163
#, php-format
msgid "%3$sFirst%4$s, prior to WordPress 5.8, go to %5$swidget%6$s administration (%1$sappearance%2$s tab), drag %1$sLumière widget%2$s (from %1$sinactive widgets%2$s) to a sidebar, and modify the box's title (in case you don't want to have the default name). As of WordPress 5.8, widgets are blocks selected by the user, and adding them is very intuitive."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:175
msgid "<strong>Second</strong>, edit your post and add the name of the movie in the box to the sidebar on your right-hand. Lumiere Movies will automatically display in the widget the movie selected."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:177
msgid "Lumière metabox to add a movie in a widget"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:182
msgid "As in many other sections of Lumière plugin, you can add the movie's IMDb id instead of the movie's title to make sure that the right movie is display. Should you want to find the movie's IMDb id, click on 'use this tool' and a new windows will be displayed; search for your movie, copy-paste its IMDb id into the sidebar, and select by 'movie id' in the dropdown list."
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:184
msgid "Lumiere Movies query interface"
msgstr ""

#: class/templates/admin/help/admin-help-howto.php:188
msgid "Using the movie's IMDb id allows more security: instead of searching for a title, Lumiere Movies can display directly the movie you are looking for. Very useful when your movie's name does not work as it should, due to movies with the same title, if a incorrect movie is displayed, etc."
msgstr ""

